    "The variables are not correlated with each other, and all are important for prediction, and acting jointly, they can give accurate results in decision trees as detailed in the Method section.",
    "We used a non-linear ensemble model for classification because the distribution of variables between classes shows that they are very similar (Fig. 2).",
    "In addition, elements in the distribution of variables by class are difficult to explain.",
    "For example, according to the organizational indicator m53_r1, stayers are in an organization with a higher proportion of perceived inequity in the distribution of delegated work.",
    "Similarly, for the m27 variable, stayers' organizations are, on average, rated as worse."
